product.longDescription: Compact, open habit with strong tipburn and bolt tolerances. Produces an impressive count of crunchy, juicy leaves that are uniform in size. Thin petioles and open habit allow leaves to separate very easily from the core. Strong structure maintains shape as a whole head, but works equally well for cut salad. NOTE: Days to maturity will vary depending on your target weight and growing practices, but you can expect a range of 35–45 days for hydroponically grown, full-size heads, or 55–60 days for field-grown heads. High resistance to downy mildew races EU 16–32, 34, 36; US 5–9 and Nasonovia ribisnigri aphid; intermediate resistance to lettuce mosaic virus. MT0-30. Pelleted seed. Avg. 12,000 seeds/lb. Packet: 25 seeds.
product.shortDescription: Exclusive! Tasty, versatile Batavia leaf type. Conventional seed with NOP-compliant pelleting.
